msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:5
msgid "Newsletter content"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:7
msgid ""
"Highlights from the Carpentries Community Calendar: Includes items from "
"The Carpentries calendar, such as upcoming events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:8
msgid ""
"Community News: A place to report on all kinds of things - events, "
"workshop or conference reports, awards, lesson releases, new reports ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:9
msgid ""
"Committee and Task Force Activity: Includes announcements directly from "
"task force and committee chairs and summaries from meeting notes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:10
msgid ""
"What you may have missed on the blog and mailing lists: Includes "
"highlights of key conversations on the Discuss email list, other lists or"
" things on the blog that need further highlighting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:11
msgid ""
"Tweet of the Week: One noteworthy tweet is chosen and a screen captured "
"image is included."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:12
msgid ""
"Optional: Papers & manuscripts for and from the community: Includes "
"announcements that were made on the Discuss email list, Twitter, or other"
" media."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:13
msgid "Optional: Offcuts: Includes other unusual news that may be of interest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:14
msgid ""
"Optional: Joinery: Includes other ways to get involved in the Carpentries"
" community and ways the Carpentries community is involved in other "
"conferences, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:15
msgid ""
"Optional: Toolshed (Posts from our Past): A place to highlight handy "
"posts from the blog or discussion list archives that might still be "
"relevant to postings to lists and other issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:16
msgid ""
"Community Job postings: Includes information that has come through on the"
" Discuss email list, Twitter, and other media."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:17
msgid ""
"Other places to connect: This section is standardized for all newsletter "
"issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:19
msgid "Submitting newsletter content"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:21
msgid ""
"Carpentries staff manage newsletter content through this private Asana "
"project.  Submissions from community members are welcome by emailing "
"newsletter@carpentries.org."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:23
msgid "Publishing the newsletter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:25
msgid ""
"This information is intended for staff or community members who have "
"taken on the responsibility of publishing the newsletter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:27
msgid "Each newsletter is a campaign on MailChimp."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:29
msgid ""
"To create a new newsletter, log in to MailChimp and click on Campaigns.  "
"Make a copy of the latest newsletter and rename the copy to reflect the "
"current date (e.g. Carpentry Clippings, 27 March, 2018.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:31
msgid ""
"Check the To field is correctly set as going to x number of newsletter "
"subscribers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:33
msgid "Check the From field is correctly set as coming from The Carpentries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:35
msgid ""
"Make sure the date in the Subject line is changed to the new newsletter "
"date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:37
msgid ""
"Select Edit design to add newsletter content. When the newsletter opens, "
"click the pencil icon in the newsletter on the left to open the "
"newsletter for editing. (Editing is all done within the right pane; the "
"left pane renders the public view as you edit.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:39
msgid ""
"Remove the old content and paste in the new, leaving the headings so that"
" the formatting for them is not disturbed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:41
msgid "Be sure to update the date at the top of the email as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:43
msgid ""
"Highlight each paragraph and click Clear styles if anything you are "
"copying in appears in bold when you don't want it to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:45
msgid ""
"Add images by clicking on the Image icon in the edit window.  All images "
"must be no more than 550px wide to render properly. These can be resized "
"within MailChimp by working with the image styling and location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:47
msgid ""
"Go to Preview and Test to preview the newsletter before sending it out. "
"This includes a desktop and mobile version preview.  Send a test email to"
" yourself to preview it in your email client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:49
msgid ""
"Save and Close and schedule the newsletter to be sent.  This should be "
"set for Wednesday at 9 am Eastern time. Be sure it is set for AM, not PM."
" A confirmation message saying \"Rock On! Your campaign has been "
"scheduled\" will be displayed, and a link to a published view of the "
"newsletter will be displayed. Paste this link into the staff channel so "
"staff have a chance to review the newsletter before it goes out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:51
msgid ""
"The newsletter will now be locked. If any changes need to be made after "
"ther newsletter has been scheduled, you will need to pause the campaign, "
"make changes, and restart the campaign."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:53
msgid ""
"After a campaign has been paused and then restarted, it is important to "
"doublecheck that the date and time for sending out the newsletter is "
"still correctly set as this will often default to the current time, "
"rather than the original scheduled time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:55
msgid ""
"As soon as the newsletter has been sent out, move it to the Carpentry "
"Clippings folder. This adds it to the searchable online archive findable "
"through our website. To move it, check the box next to the newsletter and"
" select the Carpentry Clippings folder when the Move to option appears."
msgstr ""

